In case you missed this issue of the
Saturday Evening Post, look inside and see
another recent reason why
Flying is the way to travel
and TWA is the way to fly

WEEK-END IN SWITZERLAND
From the lofty comfort of your TWA Skyliner you see the
Alps as the sun does. You sean, in close-up, the sparkling prism
of their majestic, snow-clad pinnacles, peer down at jewel-like lakes cupped
between rugged slopes. You're truly in another world —and in less than a day
since you left America for Geneva.
Yet this perfect end to a perfect day is achieved with easy unconcern
for the vast stretches of ocean and earth in between. Mastery of air trails
to Europe is routine stuff to TWA crews, who have already logged
over 40 million miles of international flying.
Yes, now if you've a mind to, you can week-end in the Alps by TWA.
Inquire of your travel agent—or any TWA office.
